



Sir,
Cambridge 19th Decr 1775.



Since writing you of this date,1 the Letter herewith Inclosed was put into my hands by Mr Eustice, who is in part the subject
[582]
of it; thinking it necessary that you should be acquainted with the contents, & a safe oppertunity offering by Mr Irwin. I do myself the honour of Inclosing it, to shew more fully to Congress the views of Lord Dunmore.2 I am Sir Yr Most Obedt Sert

Go: Washington

